vulnerability.name: USN-4234-1
vulnerability.description: Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were tricked in to opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service, obtain sensitive information, bypass Content Security Policy (CSP) restrictions, conduct cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks, or execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: Firefox could be made to crash or run programs as your login if it opened a malicious website.
